INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (11284,284,2,16,15,'15','<p>A usina hidrel&eacute;trica de Belo Monte ser&aacute; constru&iacute;da no rio Xingu, no munic&iacute;pio de Vit&oacute;ria de Xingu, no Par&aacute;. A usina ser&aacute; a terceira maior do mundo e a maior totalmente brasileira, com capacidade de 11,2 mil megawatts. Os &iacute;ndios do Xingu tomam a paisagem com seus cocares, arcos e flechas. Em Altamira, no Par&aacute;, agricultores fecharam estradas de uma regi&atilde;o que ser&aacute; inundada pelas &aacute;guas da usina.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sub><sup>BACOCCINA, D. QUEIROZ, G.: BORGES, R. <strong>Fim do leil&atilde;o, come&ccedil;o da confus&atilde;o</strong>. Isto&eacute; Dinheiro. Ano 13, n.o 655, 28 abri 2010&nbsp;(adaptado).</sup></sub><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Os impasses, resist&ecirc;ncias e desafios associados &agrave; constru&ccedil;&atilde;o da Usina Hidrel&eacute;trica de Belo Monte est&atilde;o relacionados</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (11287,349,6,25,92,'92I','<p><strong>If You Can&rsquo;t Master English, Try Globish </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>PARIS &ndash; It happens all the time: during an airport delay the man to the left, a Korean perhaps, starts talking to the man opposite, who might be Colombian, and soon they are chatting away in what seems to be English. But the native English speaker sitting between them cannot understand a word.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They don&rsquo;t know it, but the Korean and the Colombian are speaking Globish, the latest addition to the 6,800 languages that are said to be spoken across the world. Not that its inventor, Jean-Paul Nerri&egrave;re, considers it a proper language.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;It is not a language, it is a tool,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;A language is the vehicle of a culture. Globish doesn&#39;t want to be that at alI. It is a means of communication.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nerri&egrave;re doesn&#39;t see Globish in the same light as utopian efforts such as Kosmos, Volapuk, Novial or staunch Esperanto. Nor should it be confused with barbaric Algol (for Algorithmic language). It is a sort of English like: a means of simplifying the language and giving it rules so it can be understood by all.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>BLUME, M. Dispon&iacute;vel em: www.nytimes.com. Acesso em: 28 out, 2013 (fragmento). </sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Considerando as ideias apresentadas no texto, o Globish (Global English) &eacute; uma variedade da l&iacute;ngua inglesa que</p>\r\n');
