INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (12690,224,6,22,48,'48','<img src=\"https://img.enem.appprova.com.br/questions/images/12690/original/Captura_de_Tela_2015-05-23_às_14.01.47.png\" /><p>A libera&ccedil;&atilde;o dos gases clorofluocarbonos (CFCs) na atmosfera pode provocar deple&ccedil;&atilde;o de oz&ocirc;nio (O<sub>3</sub>) na estratosfera. O oz&ocirc;nio estratosf&eacute;rico &eacute; respons&aacute;vel por absorver parte da radia&ccedil;&atilde;o ultravioleta emitida pelo Sol, a qual &eacute; nociva aos seres vivos. Esse processo, na camada de oz&ocirc;nio, &eacute; ilustrado simplificadamente na imagem.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Quimicamente, a destrui&ccedil;&atilde;o do oz&ocirc;nio na atmosfera por gases CFCs &eacute; decorr&ecirc;ncia da</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (12708,267,6,25,93,'93I','<p><strong>A Tall Order</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<em>The Sky isn&rsquo;t the limit for an architect building the world&rsquo;s first invisible skyscraper.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nCharles Wee, one of the world&rsquo;s leading high&ndash;rise architects, has a confession to make: he&rsquo;s bored with skyscrapers. After designing more than 30, most of which punctuate the skylines of rapidly expanding Asian cities, he has struck upon a novel concept: the first invisible skyscraper.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nAs the tallest structure in South Kora, his infinity Tower will loom over Seoul until somebody pushes a button and it completely disappears.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nWhen he entered a 2004 competition to desing a landmark tower, the Korean&ndash;American architect rejected the notion of competing with Dubai, Toronto, and Shangai to reach the summit of man&ndash;made summits. &ldquo;I thought, let&rsquo;s not jump into this stupid race to build another &ldquo;tallest&rdquo; tower, he says in a phone conversation. &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s take an opposite approach &ndash; let&rsquo;s make an anti&ndash;tower.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe result will be a 150&ndash;story building that fades from view at the flick of a switch. The tower will effectively function as an enormous television screen, being able to project an exact replica of whatever is happening behind it onto its fa&ccedil;ade. To the human eye, the building will appear to have melted away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nIt will be the most extraordinary achievement of Wee&rsquo;s stellar architectural career. After graduating from UCLA, he worked under Anthony Lumsden, a prolific Californian architect who helped devise the modern technique of wrapping buildings inside smooth glass skins.<br />\r\n<sub>HINES, N. Dispon&iacute;vel em: http://mag.newsweek.com. Acesso em 13 out 2013 (adaptado).</sub><br />\r\n<br />\r\nNo t&iacute;tulo e no subt&iacute;tulo desse texto, as express&otilde;es&nbsp;<em>A Tall Order e The sky isn&rsquo;t the limit</em>&nbsp;s&atilde;o usadas para apresentar uma mat&eacute;ria cujo tema &eacute;&nbsp;</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (12709,349,6,25,94,'94I','<p><strong>Masters of War</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Come you masters of war<br />\r\nYou that build all the guns<br />\r\nYou that build the death planes<br />\r\nYou that build and all the bombs<br />\r\nYou that hide behind walls<br />\r\nYou that hide behind desks<br />\r\nI just want you to know<br />\r\nI can see through your masks.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou that never done nothin&rsquo;<br />\r\nBut build to destroy<br />\r\nYou play with my world<br />\r\nLike it&rsquo;s your little toy<br />\r\nYou put a gun in my hand<br />\r\nAnd you hide from my eyes<br />\r\nAnd you turn and run farther<br />\r\nWhen the fast bullets fly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLike Judas of old<br />\r\nYou lie and deceive<br />\r\nA world war can be won<br />\r\nYou want me to believe<br />\r\nBut I see through your eyes<br />\r\nAnd I see through your brain<br />\r\nLike I see through the water<br />\r\nThat runs down my drain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>BOB DYLAN. The Freewheelin&rsquo; Bob Dylan. Nova York: Columbia Records, 1963 (fragmento).</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nNa letra da can&ccedil;&atilde;o <em>Master of War</em>, h&aacute; questionamentos e reflex&otilde;es que aparecem na forma de protesto contra</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (12710,312,6,25,95,'95I','<p><strong>The road not Taken (by Robert Frost)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Two roads diverged in a wood, and I &ndash;<br />\r\nI took the one less traveled by,<br />\r\nAnd that has made all the difference.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>Dispon&iacute;vel em: www.poetryfundation.org. Aesso em: 29 nov. 2011 (fragmento).</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nEstes s&atilde;o os versos finais do famoso poema&nbsp;<em>The Road Not Taken</em>, do poeta americano Robert Frost. Levando-se em considera&ccedil;&atilde;o que a vida &eacute; comumente metaforizada como uma viagem, esses versos indicam que o autor</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (12711,312,6,26,96,'91E','<p><strong>Emigrantes</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Em todo emigrante existen dos posibles actitudes vitales: una de la considerar su experi&ecirc;ncia como aventura pasajera, vivir mental y emocionalmente en la p&aacute;tria de origen, cultivando su nostalgia, y definir la realidade presente por comparaci&oacute;n com el mundo que se ha dejado; la outra es vivir el presente tal como viene dado, proyerctarlo en el futuro, cortar raices y dominar nostalgias, sumergirse em la nueva cultura, aprenderla y asimilarla. El drama personal del emigrante reside em el hecho de que casi nunca es posible esa elecci&oacute;n em t&eacute;rminos absolutos y, al igual que el mestizo, se siente parte de dos mundos sin integrarse por completo em uno de ellos com exclusi&oacute;n del outro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><sub>DEL CASTILLO, G.C. Am&eacute;rica hisp&acirc;nica (1492-1892) In: DE LARA, M. T. HISTORIA DE ESPA&Ntilde;A. Barcelona: Labor, 1985.</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nO texto apresenta uma reflex&atilde;o sobre a condi&ccedil;&atilde;o do imigrante, o qual, para o autor, tem de lidar com o dilema</p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`,`skill_id`,`exam_id`,`subject_id`,`position`,`label`,`content`) VALUES (12712,275,6,26,97,'92E','<p>Em um a&ntilde;o de campa&ntilde;a paraguaya, he visto muchas cosas tristes...</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He visto la tierra, com su fertilidade incoercible y salvaje, sofocar al hombre, que arroja uma semilla y obtirne cien plantas diferentes y no abe c&uacute;al es la suya. He visto los viejos caminhos que abri&oacute; la tirania devorados por la vegetaci&oacute;n, desle&iacute;dos por las innundaciones, borrados por el abandono.<br />\r\n<sub>BARRET, R. Lo que visto. Cuba: XX feira internacional del libro de la Habana, 2011.</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nRafael Barret nasceu na Espanha e, ainda jovem, foi viver no Paraguai. O fragmento do texto&nbsp;<em>Lo que he visto</em>&nbsp;revela um pouco da percep&ccedil;&atilde;o do escritor sobre a realidade paraguaia, marcada, em ess&ecirc;ncia pelo(a)</p>\r\n');
